1
00:00:46,821 --> 00:00:50,215
=Love Actually S5=

2
00:00:50,360 --> 00:00:52,080
(Previously)
The girl made the first move this time.

3
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,960
Can we have dinner together tonight?

4
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:54,600
Sure.

5
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:56,320
(She's super forward.)

6
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:58,320
Let's write something memorable.

7
00:00:58,320 --> 00:00:59,280
TTBK.

8
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:00,320
TT.

9
00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:01,680
Beginnings demand the most.

10
00:01:03,640 --> 00:01:05,000
Sir, please drive faster.

11
00:01:05,240 --> 00:01:06,440
Please go faster.

12
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:07,080
Hello.

13
00:01:07,080 --> 00:01:08,360
Hello.

14
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:09,600
Do you find me attractive?

15
00:01:09,960 --> 00:01:10,280
Yes.

16
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:11,760
Do you like the way I look?

17
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:13,440
Yes, I do.

18
00:01:16,520 --> 00:01:17,240
Liu.

19
00:01:17,320 --> 00:01:17,960
Who's calling?

20
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,480
The domineering CEO is here.

21
00:01:21,360 --> 00:01:23,080
The domineering CEO is here.

22
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:24,840
Oh, my!

23
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:25,720
I'll take her home.

24
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:27,120
Why didn't you just walk in?

25
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:29,080
Just teasing her.

26
00:01:29,920 --> 00:01:31,760
So your task today is to take her home?

27
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:34,120
Yes, after you're done.

28
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:35,800
Sure, you have to wait until we're done.

29
00:01:38,440 --> 00:01:39,480
Things got interesting.

30
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,080
"Things got interesting."

31
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:43,680
What's Xiaowen doing?

32
00:01:43,680 --> 00:01:44,240
I don't know.

33
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:47,600
No one answered.

34
00:01:48,398 --> 00:01:50,478
(Where did Xiao Wentao
and Jia Peixuan go?)

35
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:56,120
You didn't find the shuttlecocks?

36
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:56,560
Not like that.

37
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:58,200
The shuttlecocks are there,
but he isn't.

38
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,080
What does that mean?

39
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:02,920
What's Xiaowen doing?

40
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:03,320
No idea.

41
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:04,640
Let's go.

42
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:04,960
Let's go.

43
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,160
The two of them...

44
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:07,760
Probably went out.

45
00:02:09,920 --> 00:02:11,200
Two rackets are missing.

46
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:13,080
There are four rackets in total,

47
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:13,720
but now two are gone.

48
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:16,120
What?

49
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:17,440
Did Xiaowen and she

50
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:18,120
take two?

51
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:21,200
He probably felt

52
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:22,120
we were taking too long.

53
00:02:22,720 --> 00:02:23,360
Where did you say

54
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:23,720
Xiaowen go?

55
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:24,600
He's gone playing badminton.

56
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:25,160
He's already playing?

57
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:26,720
He took the rackets and went ahead.

58
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,120
(Xiao Wentao's Room)
Xiaowen and Xuan

59
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:29,120
went out on their own?

60
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,920
(Jia Peixuan's Room)
It's possible.

61
00:02:31,968 --> 00:02:39,872
(Ten minutes ago)

62
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:45,240
Shuttlecocks are here.

63
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:46,440
Are you playing?

64
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:47,760
Are there a lot of people?

65
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:49,560
If there are, you wouldn't want to go?

66
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:53,760
Then let's sneak out
from the second floor.

67
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:56,480
Sneak out?

68
00:02:58,680 --> 00:03:00,280
Sneak out.

69
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:02,440
Not bad.

70
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:05,240
Then let's sneak out
from the second floor.

71
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:06,520
Alright.

72
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:08,680
You decide.

73
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:10,000
I'm fine either way.

74
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,360
Okay, I'll get the rackets first.

75
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:12,320
Okay.

76
00:03:14,083 --> 00:03:17,024
(Sneaking in quietly)

77
00:03:17,251 --> 00:03:18,920
(Rackets)
Feels like 'Fight Back to School.'

78
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:20,120
Right.

79
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:22,360
(Sneaking in quietly)
So romantic.

80
00:03:28,839 --> 00:03:30,320
(A feint)

81
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:31,480
A feint.

82
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:32,320
Looks so natural.

83
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:34,520
(Sneaking out quietly)
Very strategic.

84
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:35,880
Gently he leaves.

85
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:40,640
I got them.

86
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:47,240
We're practically sneaking like thieves.

87
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:48,440
Funny.

88
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,560
Why are they sneaking?

89
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:52,360
Want some alone time.

90
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:55,600
What? What's so funny?

91
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:56,760
You. You look like...

92
00:03:58,560 --> 00:03:59,640
Let's walk around

93
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:00,720
and look for open space.

94
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:01,120
Okay.

95
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:02,520
Forget them.

96
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:05,560
"Forget them."

97
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:06,880
Xiao Wentao's a planner.

98
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:09,560
I felt really hot inside.

99
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:10,640
Then we'll likely sweat a lot

100
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:12,040
when we play later.

101
00:04:12,040 --> 00:04:13,000
It's still quite hot.

102
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:13,720
True.

103
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,840
How are you feeling these days?

104
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:17,640
Feeling about what?

105
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:19,360
Like, within this atmosphere?

106
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:24,440
Well, I think...

107
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,960
I sometimes feel like being alone

108
00:04:26,960 --> 00:04:28,400
or spending time privately with someone.

109
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:29,680
I just didn't feel like...

110
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,120
I get it.

111
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:31,320
Group hanging out.

112
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,080
Sometimes,

113
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:35,920
I just want to go out at night

114
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:38,480
to take a lakeside walk.

115
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:42,000
I invited you out for a game today.

116
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,200
So I really wanted out now.

117
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:44,680
I didn't want to stay indoors.

118
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:47,480
Weren't you out yesterday?

119
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:50,720
Yeah.

120
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:51,920
Yes, yesterday...

121
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:54,560
Horse riding.

122
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,160
Was it fun?

123
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:57,760
Riding was fun.

124
00:04:58,440 --> 00:04:59,600
But we can't

125
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:00,960
refuse tasks now.

126
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,680
(He was just doing the task.)

127
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:04,480
What? Were you going to refuse?

128
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:08,280
Well, yesterday I wasn't super keen
on going out.

129
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:09,360
Why didn't you want to go out yesterday,

130
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:10,200
but you do today?

131
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:12,240
Because yesterday,

132
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:13,400
I spent the afternoon practicing.

133
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:16,760
So basically yesterday,

134
00:05:16,760 --> 00:05:18,160
I needed to be alone in my room.

135
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:20,280
So when I came back last night,

136
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:21,440
I was pretty worn out.

137
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,520
Really?

138
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:25,560
I heard you and her

139
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:27,440
talking and laughing as you came in.

140
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:29,240
I was in the lounge and overheard.

141
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,880
I was wondering
whether to come out or not.

142
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:32,160
Then I heard someone say

143
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:33,760
something about me doing something.

144
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:34,800
If I didn't come out,

145
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:37,000
it might seem like I was eavesdropping

146
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:37,720
or something.

147
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:44,000
She kept pushing him away.

148
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,160
She's someone
who doesn't have a strong safety net.

149
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:46,960
She needs reassurance.

150
00:05:46,960 --> 00:05:48,080
Absolute reassurance.

151
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:51,000
Anyway, I thought horse riding was fun.

152
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:52,560
Have you ever ridden before?

153
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:53,160
No.

154
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:53,840
It was my first time.

155
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:55,680
So, how did you chat

156
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:58,240
while riding horses?

157
00:05:58,240 --> 00:05:59,360
Were the horses side by side?

158
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:00,080
There was no chatting.

159
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:01,080
Look, here's what happened.

160
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:04,120
We tried to ride alongside each other.

161
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:04,640
Right.

162
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:06,520
But my horse was so stubborn.

163
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:07,920
Just so stubborn.

164
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,200
It kept charging ahead.

165
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:09,960
It wouldn't cooperate.

166
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:11,000
And the horse she was on

167
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,280
was kind of slow and tired.

168
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:14,920
So there wasn't much to talk about

169
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:16,080
during the ride.

170
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:18,680
He's constantly reassuring her,

171
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:20,400
like, "We actually didn't talk much."

172
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:22,840
Okay.

173
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:25,160
I didn't get anything out of that.

174
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,160
What do you

175
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:26,760
want to know?

176
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:27,360
Just say it.

177
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:28,120
What do you want to know?

178
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:30,200
I'm just curious
what you two talked about.

179
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:30,920
We...

180
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:32,920
chatted about movies and music.

181
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,160
Just friendly conversation.

182
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:37,720
Very friendly.

183
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:39,000
Friendly.

184
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:40,440
Good.

185
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:42,840
But we couldn't stop you guys
from teasing.

186
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,160
Who was easing?

187
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:45,040
You mean I was teasing?

188
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:45,880
Who was teasing?

189
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:46,960
Who was teasing?

190
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:49,360
Listen to yourself.

191
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:50,800
Who was teasing?

192
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:52,400
When did I ever tease?

193
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:58,040
They are in perfect harmony.

194
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,880
Shining brightly.

195
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:03,200
Last night it was endless.

196
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:05,120
The teasing just wouldn't stop.

197
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,240
What?

198
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:06,800
What?

199
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:09,400
You two really seemed to click.

200
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,200
Didn't you think that scene

201
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,480
looked really good?

202
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,520
But I play with lots of people.

203
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:17,720
We're all just hanging out.

204
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:18,960
I think it's normal.

205
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:20,240
Playing together is just playing.

206
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:21,800
So your stance now is

207
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:22,880
that you don't want her
to misunderstand?

208
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:24,240
I don't want her to misunderstand.

209
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:26,360
We can all be good friends.

210
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:28,800
You've already defined her as a friend?

211
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:30,880
(His stance right now is key.)

212
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:31,520
(Right.)

213
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:38,920
So fast?

214
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:40,920
(Xuan's womanly side is showing.)

215
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,120
(Right.)

216
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,040
You're silent again.

217
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,200
Well, do you know...

218
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:49,680
Never mind, I don't know.

219
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:50,480
Spit it out.

220
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:51,640
Now I'm stammering.

221
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:52,600
I don't know what to say.

222
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:53,360
Come on, I want to hear it.

223
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:55,320
"I want to hear it."

224
00:07:55,320 --> 00:07:56,400
Fantastic.

225
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,000
Okay, I get it.

226
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,560
I'll tone it down next time.

227
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,280
I see what you mean.

228
00:08:01,280 --> 00:08:02,240
Next time I'll hold back a bit.

229
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,200
There's a next time?

230
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:06,320
If I don't tease, they will.

231
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:08,560
Right?

232
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:13,040
When feelings are mutual,

233
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:14,600
everything seems delightful.

234
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:16,480
Sit down?

235
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:17,560
Sure.

236
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:18,960
On Chen Jianying's

237
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:20,080
first night here,

238
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:22,080
maybe she was out of choices,

239
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:22,840
so she picked me.

240
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:23,520
No.

241
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:24,520
It's not like that.

242
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:25,240
No?

243
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,880
Yesterday or some other time,

244
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:27,560
she told me.

245
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,040
She said you

246
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:32,120
were the one she found appealing.

247
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:34,000
So she asked you out.

248
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:35,600
That's something...

249
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:38,560
I like girls like that.

250
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:39,440
Direct.

251
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:40,040
Very direct.

252
00:08:40,040 --> 00:08:40,880
It's better to be direct.

253
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,600
I'm tired of beating around the bush.

254
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:43,280
It's pointless.

255
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:44,600
All that ambiguity

256
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:47,240
is such a waste of time.

257
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,360
So, if it were you,

258
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,560
would you beat around the bush,

259
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:50,440
or just go for it directly?

260
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:53,200
When I meet people for the first time,

261
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,480
I'll be quite direct.

262
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:55,960
I'll say who I find appealing.

263
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:56,960
Maybe I will...

264
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:57,880
Who's appealing to you?

265
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:02,560
You're trying to trap me.

266
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:04,920
I asked you out today.

267
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:10,960
They're so cute.

268
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,520
So you found me appealing?

269
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,200
Exactly.

270
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,600
Yes, that's why I asked you out.

271
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:20,360
Look. Today

272
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:22,120
I asked directly
if you wanted to play badminton.

273
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:23,960
Yeah, I know.

274
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:27,200
So you'll keep her
at a distance from now on?

275
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,000
Is that what you mean?

276
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:30,400
Yeah, I might need to avoid

277
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,960
those one-on-one moments.

278
00:09:33,920 --> 00:09:34,840
I'll shorten the time

279
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,440
we spend alone.

280
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:40,200
Their straightforwardness
makes things pressure-free.

281
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,400
(So wonderful.)

282
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,640
People keep thinking

283
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:45,720
Chen Jianying and I

284
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:47,960
might become an item.

285
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:50,160
Earlier today, I told Xuan

286
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:51,560
about my thoughts.

287
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:54,960
I told her what's actually

288
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:55,600
on my mind.

289
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:57,360
It felt good.

290
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:59,200
I don't want her to misunderstand.

291
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:00,920
I hope

292
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:02,840
everyone understands my take on this.

