(Yesterday afternoon)
Can you make tomato scrambled eggs?

582
00:18:31,600 --> 00:18:33,360
I'm totally great at that!

583
00:18:33,360 --> 00:18:35,160
Whenever I go to a homestyle restaurant,

584
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:37,200
I have to order tomato scrambled eggs.

585
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,440
(And he made it today.)

586
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:39,160
I'm making...

587
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:41,400
Do you guys eat
sweet tomato scrambled eggs?

588
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:42,320
It's zero-calorie sugar.

589
00:18:42,320 --> 00:18:42,800
Yeah.

590
00:18:42,800 --> 00:18:43,520
No problem.

591
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:44,960
She feels like he made it for her.

592
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:46,600
Yes, she thinks it's a hint.

593
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:47,000
Good.

594
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:49,040
Today, let's see

595
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:50,680
Xuan

596
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:51,920
(Today's chefs: Xiao Wentao, Jia Peixuan)
and Xiaowen show off.

597
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:54,520
You thaw like this?

598
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:54,880
Yeah.

599
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:55,320
Soak in water first.

600
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:56,160
Will this work?

601
00:18:58,360 --> 00:18:59,080
I'll do it.

602
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:02,320
It's okay, it's a bit hard.

603
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:05,480
Jealous?

604
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:12,280
Smells great!

605
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:15,240
You're amazing!

606
00:19:15,240 --> 00:19:16,200
Xiaowen.

607
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:18,000
Smells amazing!

608
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,200
So cool, really!

609
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:20,320
Smells fantastic!

610
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:23,640
You're plating?

611
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:24,840
You're so fancy!

612
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:25,800
What?

613
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,600
Are you slicing this for plating?

614
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:29,760
Yeah, it adds flavor too.

615
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:30,600
Exactly.

616
00:19:31,040 --> 00:19:32,160
A man who pays attention to details.

617
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:34,400
Not bad at all.

618
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:37,320
Let me take a picture.

619
00:19:40,120 --> 00:19:41,720
Really great!

620
00:19:41,720 --> 00:19:42,720
Come on, put your hand here too.

621
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:43,120
Hold it.

622
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:43,520
Keep your hands still.

623
00:19:44,360 --> 00:19:45,320
Your hands, back here.

624
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:45,800
Support it.

625
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:46,360
My hands?

626
00:19:46,360 --> 00:19:47,280
No, I mean...

627
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:47,840
His hands?

628
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:48,480
Yes, his hands.

629
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:52,600
(It's embarrassing.)

630
00:19:53,560 --> 00:19:54,280
Come on, your hands, don't move.

631
00:19:58,360 --> 00:19:58,640
Yes.

632
00:20:00,080 --> 00:20:00,440
Yeah.

633
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:02,160
Let's get the beautiful hands in too.

634
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:04,240
So awkward!

635
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:05,080
Indeed...

636
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:07,120
"Let's get the beautiful hands in too."

637
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,120
One, two, three.

638
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:12,880
It's so good.

639
00:20:31,880 --> 00:20:32,720
(Ruita.)

640
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:37,720
(Is she gonna get him a blanket?)

641
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:48,960
Come on!

642
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:50,720
You two should get married.

643
00:20:50,720 --> 00:20:51,760
They're so sweet!

644
00:20:56,040 --> 00:20:57,400
One of us isn't back yet.

645
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:58,680
Should we save some for her?

646
00:20:58,680 --> 00:20:59,520
Who isn't back?

647
00:21:00,480 --> 00:21:01,000
Guess.

648
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:02,720
Oh, I know, Xu Lvyang.

649
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:03,880
She went home
to pack up her things, right?

650
00:21:03,880 --> 00:21:05,120
Yes, we should set some aside for her.

651
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:06,960
Try not to mess up its look.

652
00:21:08,360 --> 00:21:09,680
(Ling is doing great.)

653
00:21:18,535 --> 00:21:20,192
(Glances at the time)

654
00:21:20,840 --> 00:21:21,520
There's a draft.

655
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:22,600
It's kind of chilly, guys.

656
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:23,360
Are you cold?

657
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:25,600
We'll close it after we're done cooking.

658
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:26,840
Okay.

659
00:21:33,120 --> 00:21:34,680
Ling has been distracted all day long.

660
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:37,480
(Liu hasn't come back yet.)

661
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:38,280
(So,)

662
00:21:38,280 --> 00:21:39,680
(I just wanted to wait for her outside.)

663
00:21:41,080 --> 00:21:42,520
(And this afternoon I was thinking)

664
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:44,080
(about when she'll come back.)

665
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:45,280
(And then I thought,)

666
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:47,360
(I'd like to carry her luggage.)

667
00:21:47,360 --> 00:21:48,680
(Because her luggage
must be pretty heavy.)

668
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:51,680
(So I tried to estimate
when she'd return.)

669
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:54,720
(Once she's back,
I can help with her bags.)

670
00:21:55,840 --> 00:21:57,520
(He wants to be the first
to welcome her back?)

671
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:58,280
(Yeah.)

672
00:21:58,520 --> 00:22:00,680
I completely understand that feeling

673
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:01,720
of wanting to wait for your crush.

674
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:02,680
He just wants that very first moment,

675
00:22:02,680 --> 00:22:03,320
even just that split second,

676
00:22:03,320 --> 00:22:04,400
to be seen by her.

677
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:38,120
(She's coming.)

678
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:45,920
(He can't stop smiling.)

679
00:22:45,920 --> 00:22:47,560
How did you know I was coming back?

680
00:22:47,560 --> 00:22:48,960
Happened to be
taking a stroll around here,

681
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:49,520
and I came over to have a look.

682
00:22:49,520 --> 00:22:51,240
You just went out for a walk?

683
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:52,120
Yes.

684
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:53,840
I just happened to come back.

685
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:54,680
What a coincidence!

686
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:56,600
You have luggage?

687
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:56,880
I do.

688
00:22:56,880 --> 00:22:57,640
I can help you carry it.

689
00:23:01,600 --> 00:23:02,400
What a coincidence.

690
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:03,080
Indeed.

691
00:23:03,080 --> 00:23:04,560
Which way did you go for your walk?

692
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:05,880
I just wanted some fresh air outside.

693
00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:06,720
It's really heavy.

694
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:07,200
I got this.

695
00:23:08,240 --> 00:23:09,120
It's okay, I got this.

696
00:23:09,120 --> 00:23:09,960
Thank you.

697
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:10,640
Thank you so much.

698
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:15,320
Welcome back.

699
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:16,800
Thanks.

700
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:17,520
Shall we?

701
00:23:17,520 --> 00:23:18,600
Let's go.

702
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:21,120
Haven't had dinner yet?

703
00:23:21,120 --> 00:23:21,400
No.

704
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:22,320
Have you all finished eating?

705
00:23:22,320 --> 00:23:22,680
Not yet.

706
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:24,720
I thought you might be back later.

707
00:23:24,720 --> 00:23:25,920
They just cooked something,

708
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:28,960
So I saved some chicken for you.

709
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:30,640
But we haven't started eating. Yeah.

710
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:32,360
Anyway, we are all waiting for you.

711
00:23:33,080 --> 00:23:34,040
That's so sweet!

712
00:23:36,280 --> 00:23:36,640
Tired?

713
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:38,880
A little bit.

714
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:41,440
I finished packing right away
and rushed back.

715
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:42,200
Hi, everyone!

716
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:43,520
You're back! Liu!

717
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:44,760
Really, what a coincidence for us.

718
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:46,080
We caught them red-handed.

719
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:46,480
Yeah.

720
00:23:46,480 --> 00:23:48,160
Don't disturb them.

721
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:49,040
Just sit down.

722
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:49,560
Come on.

723
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:50,000
Sit down.

724
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:50,720
Pretend we didn't see them.

725
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:51,600
Didn't see them.

726
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:51,880
Just a sec.

727
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:52,600
I'll take this away.

728
00:23:53,080 --> 00:23:54,400
It is so windy today.

729
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:56,000
Aren't you guys cold here?

730
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,200
We just wanted to get some fresh air.

731
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:58,280
Want to join us?

732
00:23:58,280 --> 00:23:58,960
It's warm inside.

733
00:23:58,960 --> 00:23:59,360
But,

734
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:01,320
the hall might get a draft.

735
00:24:01,320 --> 00:24:02,240
Why don't you change your jacket?

736
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:03,600
We are sitting over here...

737
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:05,120
So this is how it feels
to watch the drama unfold.

738
00:24:05,120 --> 00:24:05,600
Really.

739
00:24:06,080 --> 00:24:08,320
Just our luck to run into this today.

740
00:24:08,320 --> 00:24:10,160
They're so sweet.

741
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:12,160
These two are quite amusing.

742
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:14,120
Just bumped into this

743
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:15,200
and wanted to pretend not to have seen.

744
00:24:17,160 --> 00:24:17,720
Hello.

745
00:24:18,280 --> 00:24:19,960
The new guest is back.

746
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:21,360
Hello everyone.

747
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:22,840
I'm the new female guest arriving today.

748
00:24:22,840 --> 00:24:23,560
Welcome.

749
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:26,600
Xiao Wentao did a ton of things today.

750
00:24:29,040 --> 00:24:30,160
Today, we played badminton.

751
00:24:30,160 --> 00:24:31,560
Then we prepared dishes the whole time.

752
00:24:31,560 --> 00:24:32,000
Yeah.

753
00:24:32,560 --> 00:24:33,760
Who's sleeping there?

754
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:34,520
No idea.

755
00:24:36,320 --> 00:24:36,960
Okay.

756
00:24:37,360 --> 00:24:37,960
Much appreciated.

757
00:24:37,960 --> 00:24:38,800
I'll leave you here.

758
00:24:38,800 --> 00:24:39,920
See you downstairs.

759
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:40,960
Okay, thanks.

760
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:42,400
I'll put my things away first,
and then I'll come down.

761
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:43,800
Remember to put on a jacket.

762
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:44,080
Okay.

763
00:24:44,880 --> 00:24:45,600
How thoughtful.

764
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:46,400
It's nice.

765
00:24:49,040 --> 00:24:51,080
Alright, Zhou Youling is awake.

766
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:02,560
I was about to knock on your door

767
00:25:02,560 --> 00:25:04,040
and you directly opened it.

768
00:25:04,880 --> 00:25:05,960
Well, what's wrong?

769
00:25:05,960 --> 00:25:08,080
I nicked my nose
with the razor this morning.

770
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:09,040
It bled.

771
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:09,800
It's a bit swollen now.

772
00:25:10,840 --> 00:25:11,680
Then take care of it.

773
00:25:12,520 --> 00:25:13,120
Where did you go?

774
00:25:13,520 --> 00:25:14,640
I went home to get my luggage.

775
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:16,840
Then you handle that first.

776
00:25:17,680 --> 00:25:18,800
Why did you knock my door?

777
00:25:20,240 --> 00:25:20,640
Nothing.

778
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:21,320
To see what you were doing.

779
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:22,760
I was asleep just now.

780
00:25:23,400 --> 00:25:23,920
Then take more rest.

781
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:25,760
I'm coming down.

782
00:25:29,063 --> 00:25:29,920
(Adjusts)

783
00:25:30,344 --> 00:25:30,966
(Appearance)

784
00:25:34,360 --> 00:25:35,320
Hello.

785
00:25:35,320 --> 00:25:36,080
Hello.

786
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:39,200
Liu caught a great time.

787
00:25:39,760 --> 00:25:41,560
Lucky me.

788
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:44,080
Tell everyone dinner's ready.

789
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:44,840
Call everyone.

790
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:45,880
Call them.

791
00:25:46,360 --> 00:25:48,600
Dinner's up, guys!

792
00:25:48,600 --> 00:25:49,320
Dinner is ready.

793
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:50,360
Coming.

794
00:25:50,640 --> 00:25:52,440
Let's toast to Xiao Wentao.

795
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:53,280
Thanks.

796
00:25:53,280 --> 00:25:54,240
Come on.

797
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:56,280
You look so graceful, babe.

798
00:25:57,320 --> 00:25:59,520
Great sleep, great shower.

799
00:26:01,800 --> 00:26:02,520
How long did you sleep?

800
00:26:03,040 --> 00:26:03,480
I'm not sure.

801
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:04,360
I just lay down and fell asleep.

802
00:26:06,160 --> 00:26:07,240
Oh, the box of meat

803
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:08,640
Ling Lizheng

804
00:26:08,640 --> 00:26:10,360
saved for Liu.

805
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:12,520
Zhou Youling's expression.

806
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:14,000
What does it mean?

807
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:15,360
I put it back.

808
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:16,280
What?

809
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:17,680
Because you weren't here.

810
00:26:17,680 --> 00:26:18,560
And everyone was here.

811
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:19,400
So I specifically...

812
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:21,080
Yeah, he served a box just for you.

813
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:22,760
Exclusively.

814
00:26:22,760 --> 00:26:24,200
Then I saw you were back

815
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:25,000
before everyone started eating.

816
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:26,320
So I put it back on the table.

817
00:26:26,760 --> 00:26:27,840
Hastily put it back.

818
00:26:28,264 --> 00:26:30,944
(20 minutes ago)

819
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:34,080
Thank you so much!

820
00:26:46,080 --> 00:26:47,880
End of scene for this part, guys!

821
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:49,200
First and foremost, I really have to

822
00:26:49,200 --> 00:26:50,600
give credit to Xiaowen.

823
00:26:50,600 --> 00:26:51,640
Give him a thumbs up.

824
00:26:51,640 --> 00:26:52,000
Yes.

825
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:53,600
Excellent.

826
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:54,320
Have you ever,

827
00:26:54,320 --> 00:26:55,960
regardless of the relationship,

828
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:57,360
been in that moment,

829
00:26:57,360 --> 00:26:58,320
the moment of being firmly chosen?

830
00:26:58,320 --> 00:26:59,200
You mean, favored?

831
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:00,920
Yes, being favored.

832
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:02,160
Steadfast favoritism.

833
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:03,640
My most steadfast favoritism recently

834
00:27:03,640 --> 00:27:04,320
is from my son.

835
00:27:04,880 --> 00:27:05,240
Go ahead.

836
00:27:05,640 --> 00:27:06,800
In our family,

837
00:27:06,800 --> 00:27:07,680
we often play a game.

838
00:27:07,680 --> 00:27:09,120
They were so young then.

839
00:27:09,120 --> 00:27:11,400
Like when we played

840
00:27:11,400 --> 00:27:13,800
the cops and robbers game,

841
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:15,520
my son was a policeman, and he went out.

842
00:27:15,520 --> 00:27:17,720
In the room,
there might have been a donut.

843
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:19,440
Then one of us ate

844
00:27:19,440 --> 00:27:20,120
this donut.

845
00:27:20,120 --> 00:27:21,280
So he came in to solve the case,

846
00:27:21,280 --> 00:27:22,480
asking who ate it.

847
00:27:23,040 --> 00:27:24,480
Even if I had chocolate

848
00:27:24,480 --> 00:27:25,320
on my lips

849
00:27:25,320 --> 00:27:27,080
or powdered sugar on my hands,

850
00:27:27,080 --> 00:27:28,320
and he saw it,

851
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:29,240
he always said

852
00:27:29,240 --> 00:27:30,200
my husband was the thief.

853
00:27:32,640 --> 00:27:33,960
Because he doesn't wanna accuse his mom.

854
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:35,480
Yeah, it was pretty obvious.

855
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:36,880
But my son still insisted.

856
00:27:36,880 --> 00:27:37,840
He always favors you.

857
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:38,760
Exactly.

858
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,032
(That's sweet)

859
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:41,640
That's so adorable.

860
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:42,680
Yeah.

861
00:27:43,120 --> 00:27:45,040
But in this semi-mature age phase,

862
00:27:45,040 --> 00:27:47,680
unwavering favoritism
is actually quite rare.

863
00:27:47,680 --> 00:27:49,120
Because everyone tends to have a bit

864
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:52,000
of an adult's excessive...

865
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:53,040
(Politeness)
Politeness and self-respect.

866
00:27:53,040 --> 00:27:53,560
(Self-respect)
Yeah.

867
00:27:53,560 --> 00:27:54,760
But that just turns everything
overly polite.

868
00:27:54,760 --> 00:27:55,440
Yeah.

869
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:56,320
Extremely polite.

870
00:27:56,320 --> 00:27:56,680
Yeah.

871
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:57,600
At this semi-mature age,

872
00:27:57,600 --> 00:27:59,800
people tend to consider
or weigh many things.

873
00:27:59,800 --> 00:28:00,560
But his...

874
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:01,320
Xiaowen's

875
00:28:01,320 --> 00:28:02,680
boldly upfront approach

876
00:28:02,680 --> 00:28:04,040
is exceptionally valuable.

877
00:28:04,040 --> 00:28:04,560
Pretty cool.

878
00:28:04,560 --> 00:28:05,080
Very admirable.

879
00:28:05,880 --> 00:28:07,200
Just now there was
another really cute moment,

880
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,320
scrambled eggs with tomatoes.

881
00:28:08,320 --> 00:28:09,720
Let's connect it all.

882
00:28:09,720 --> 00:28:11,680
The phrase mentioned
in the previous clip,

883
00:28:11,680 --> 00:28:12,760
something he posted in his Moments.

884
00:28:12,760 --> 00:28:14,320
When two people read
the exact same words,

885
00:28:14,320 --> 00:28:16,240
Jia Peixuan didn't think it necessarily

886
00:28:16,640 --> 00:28:17,320
referred to her.

887
00:28:17,320 --> 00:28:17,920
She doubted it.

888
00:28:17,920 --> 00:28:18,920
Denied it.

889
00:28:18,920 --> 00:28:19,880
But Chen Jianying

890
00:28:19,880 --> 00:28:21,280
felt certain it was about her.

891
00:28:22,013 --> 00:28:23,160
(Had fun horseback riding today.
How was your day?)

892
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:23,960
(This phrase,)

893
00:28:23,960 --> 00:28:25,520
(I really, really love it.)

894
00:28:26,600 --> 00:28:27,880
(I'm not sure.)

895
00:28:28,320 --> 00:28:29,880
(Unsure about whom)

896
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:31,280
(it refers to.)

897
00:28:31,960 --> 00:28:33,720
Given your distinct personalities,

898
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:34,560
when faced

899
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:35,680
with such gestures of affection,

900
00:28:35,680 --> 00:28:36,480
which type

901
00:28:36,480 --> 00:28:37,720
would you be more like?

902
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:39,640
Hearing this question reminds me

903
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:41,040
of a joke I heard before.

904
00:28:41,040 --> 00:28:42,800
About how women generally

905
00:28:42,800 --> 00:28:44,080
interpret things.

906
00:28:44,080 --> 00:28:45,440
Like, he bought me breakfast today,

907
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:46,560
is he into me?

908
00:28:46,560 --> 00:28:47,960
He queued up to buy medicine for me.

909
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:49,200
Does he have a crush on me?

910
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:50,400
Men, on the other hand, just think,

911
00:28:51,960 --> 00:28:52,960
like, she didn't tell me
to get lost today,

912
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:53,800
is she into me now?

913
00:28:55,720 --> 00:28:56,600
Yeah.

914
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:58,080
The baseline standards
are completely different.

915
00:28:59,160 --> 00:29:00,880
Many of my good male friends

916
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:01,720
would say,

917
00:29:01,720 --> 00:29:03,160
I think this girl likes me.

918
00:29:03,160 --> 00:29:04,400
I'd say, are you sure?

919
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:05,800
They'd say they were certain

920
00:29:06,840 --> 00:29:08,280
because she replied with a sticker.

921
00:29:08,280 --> 00:29:08,760
It's like...

922
00:29:08,760 --> 00:29:09,160
A meme.

923
00:29:09,160 --> 00:29:09,960
A meme.

924
00:29:09,960 --> 00:29:12,080
Whereas girls are different.

925
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:13,000
They're like,

926
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:15,560
I don't think this guy's into me.

927
00:29:15,560 --> 00:29:17,320
And I'd ask to see their chat history,

928
00:29:17,320 --> 00:29:18,960
and the guy was clearly
throwing out jokes constantly,

929
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:21,160
he just hadn't said
the words "I like you".

930
00:29:22,640 --> 00:29:24,840
That misjudgment in love is troublesome.

931
00:29:24,840 --> 00:29:26,920
Yeah, whichever direction
the misjudgment falls.

932
00:29:26,920 --> 00:29:28,080
I've misjudged before.

933
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:28,720
Please.

934
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:30,000
Well, he hadn't said he liked me.

935
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:31,760
Overall, he gave me

936
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:32,920
a bunch of gifts.

937
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:34,120
A big gift package,

938
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:35,200
snacks,

939
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:35,560
and whatever else.

940
00:29:36,080 --> 00:29:36,720
Then I said,

941
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:37,400
"Thank you, I'm so happy."

942
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:38,120
But I can't finish

943
00:29:38,120 --> 00:29:39,760
all those snacks in a day alone!

944
00:29:39,760 --> 00:29:40,840
I gave them away the same day

945
00:29:40,840 --> 00:29:42,080
to all of my girl friends.

946
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:43,680
Then he asked if I finished them all,

947
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:44,520
and I said I finished them.

948
00:29:44,520 --> 00:29:45,320
Said they were so delicious.

949
00:29:45,320 --> 00:29:46,160
Then he asked,

950
00:29:46,160 --> 00:29:47,280
"Then did you see anything?"

951
00:29:49,040 --> 00:29:50,720
Turns out he wrote a letter

952
00:29:52,080 --> 00:29:53,880
- inside it.
- Inside it.

953
00:29:53,880 --> 00:29:54,920
But I couldn't bring myself

954
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:56,560
to go ask each one for it back.

955
00:29:56,560 --> 00:29:57,440
Your friends

956
00:29:57,440 --> 00:29:58,520
probably gave away

957
00:29:58,520 --> 00:29:59,400
your snacks, too.

958
00:30:00,360 --> 00:30:02,080
None of them found that letter.

959
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:03,400
Yeah.

960
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:04,960
It really was so embarrassing.

961
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:06,160
Actually, I think,

962
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:07,560
it's not just

963
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:08,800
among the guests we've seen.

964
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:10,080
Including us in the observation room,

965
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:10,640
you'll notice

966
00:30:10,640 --> 00:30:11,560
that each person has

967
00:30:11,560 --> 00:30:13,800
a pattern for dealing
with relationships.

968
00:30:14,280 --> 00:30:16,160
In romance, we call them love scripts.

969
00:30:16,160 --> 00:30:16,920
Actually, within relationships,

970
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:18,120
there's a relationship script.

971
00:30:18,120 --> 00:30:19,520
As for Xuan herself,

972
00:30:19,520 --> 00:30:20,360
you'll see

973
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:22,880
that because she's been through divorce,

974
00:30:22,880 --> 00:30:23,800
that means

975
00:30:23,800 --> 00:30:26,040
the things that were once confirmed

976
00:30:26,040 --> 00:30:28,320
could still be taken away.

977
00:30:28,320 --> 00:30:30,080
So in all her emotional patterns,

978
00:30:30,080 --> 00:30:31,960
she's prone to anxiety
over potential loss.

979
00:30:31,960 --> 00:30:33,520
Her way of using jokes

980
00:30:33,520 --> 00:30:34,960
and teasing

981
00:30:34,960 --> 00:30:36,160
is actually her shield

982
00:30:36,160 --> 00:30:37,360
because she can't bear

983
00:30:37,360 --> 00:30:38,920
direct rejection, and she's insecure.

984
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:40,400
So she uses that approach

985
00:30:40,400 --> 00:30:42,080
to respond to problems.

986
00:30:43,080 --> 00:30:44,160
Actually, the reason I feel

987
00:30:44,160 --> 00:30:45,920
that intimate relationships
really help you grow,

988
00:30:45,920 --> 00:30:48,040
is that you see your own script.

989
00:30:48,040 --> 00:30:49,800
You see your own patterns.

990
00:30:49,800 --> 00:30:50,920
So if your love life

991
00:30:50,920 --> 00:30:52,080
keeps having problems,

992
00:30:52,080 --> 00:30:53,360
it's likely not

993
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:54,960
that you haven't met the right person,

994
00:30:54,960 --> 00:30:56,480
but rather that your pattern

995
00:30:56,480 --> 00:30:58,920
is constantly
shutting the right person out.

996
00:30:58,920 --> 00:30:59,480
So often,

997
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:01,200
it's not that you can't
meet the right person,

998
00:31:01,200 --> 00:31:03,160
but that your relationship pattern

999
00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:04,520
excludes your

1000
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:05,040
ideal match,

1001
00:31:05,040 --> 00:31:05,840
keeping them out.

1002
00:31:05,840 --> 00:31:07,760
Then Ms. Shen, could you explain for us

1003
00:31:07,760 --> 00:31:09,240
why does this happen,

1004
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:10,120
the misjudgment?

1005
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:10,640
Yeah.

1006
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:12,120
Actually, at Fudan University,

1007
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:13,760
we conducted a small experiment.

1008
00:31:14,200 --> 00:31:16,200
If someone's into you,

1009
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:17,920
what kind of signs will they show?

1010
00:31:17,920 --> 00:31:19,680
Everyone thought,

1011
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:21,240
if someone loves me,

1012
00:31:21,240 --> 00:31:22,760
their actions should be

1013
00:31:22,760 --> 00:31:24,280
very clear

1014
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:25,320
and demonstrative.

1015
00:31:25,320 --> 00:31:26,760
Yet when they spoke about

1016
00:31:26,760 --> 00:31:28,280
what they'd do when falling for others,

1017
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:31,040
they said they'd silently love them,

1018
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:32,240
definitely without any

1019
00:31:32,240 --> 00:31:34,640
of those actions
they imagined others doing.

1020
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:35,480
So you'll notice

1021
00:31:35,480 --> 00:31:36,920
many misunderstandings here occur

1022
00:31:36,920 --> 00:31:39,200
because what we imagine others would do

1023
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:40,640
and what we ourselves do

1024
00:31:40,640 --> 00:31:41,920
always have a gap.

1025
00:31:43,040 --> 00:31:45,160
Last time I worked on a show
with He Guangzhi,

1026
00:31:46,040 --> 00:31:48,160
and I mentioned a very interesting point

1027
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:49,240
from this research of ours.

1028
00:31:49,240 --> 00:31:50,320
There was this one person

1029
00:31:50,320 --> 00:31:52,040
who thought that he fell for someone,

1030
00:31:52,040 --> 00:31:53,800
and made the other person's birthday

1031
00:31:53,800 --> 00:31:55,200
his password.

1032
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:56,160
Then Guangzhi said,

1033
00:31:57,800 --> 00:31:59,000
"That's exactly what I do."

1034
00:32:00,280 --> 00:32:01,440
His phone password

1035
00:32:01,440 --> 00:32:02,160
is my birthday?

1036
00:32:04,080 --> 00:32:05,400
And we were like,

1037
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:06,920
"What's wrong with you, Guangzhi?"

1038
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:08,880
Because if you express interest

1039
00:32:08,880 --> 00:32:10,000
in a girl this way,

1040
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:11,240
come on,

1041
00:32:11,240 --> 00:32:12,720
who's going to know?

1042
00:32:12,720 --> 00:32:13,840
It's too hard.

1043
00:32:13,840 --> 00:32:15,480
Yeah, it's true that guys often

1044
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:17,960
end up doing some things
to impress themselves.

1045
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:19,200
I think,

1046
00:32:19,200 --> 00:32:20,200
you need to know

1047
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:22,160
how to express your love

1048
00:32:22,160 --> 00:32:23,760
and make what you did known

1049
00:32:23,760 --> 00:32:24,920
in a relationship.

1050
00:32:24,920 --> 00:32:26,520
When in love with someone,

1051
00:32:26,520 --> 00:32:28,360
you can't just rely on

1052
00:32:28,360 --> 00:32:29,160
your secret crush,

1053
00:32:29,160 --> 00:32:30,880
thinking about her a hundred times a day

1054
00:32:30,880 --> 00:32:31,800
and then constantly wondering

1055
00:32:31,800 --> 00:32:33,280
why she hasn't started to like you yet.

1056
00:32:35,280 --> 00:32:37,840
You absolutely need to channel
your energy in the right direction.

1057
00:32:37,840 --> 00:32:38,520
Exactly.

1058
00:32:40,160 --> 00:32:41,040
I'm full.

1059
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:42,360
Let's go have some fun!

1060
00:32:42,360 --> 00:32:43,560
Let's go.

1061
00:32:46,520 --> 00:32:46,840
Here it comes.

1062
00:32:47,760 --> 00:32:48,240
What is?

1063
00:32:50,640 --> 00:32:51,640
Exclusive to the guys.

1064
00:32:52,280 --> 00:32:54,160
(Guys' Exclusive Secret Task)
Exclusive secret mission for the guys.

1065
00:32:54,160 --> 00:32:55,240
(Guys' secret task.)

1066
00:32:55,600 --> 00:32:57,200
Please proceed to the recreation room.

1067
00:32:57,200 --> 00:32:58,280
Randomly draw one

1068
00:32:58,280 --> 00:33:00,200
of the blind box task cards
on the coffee table.

1069
00:33:00,680 --> 00:33:02,760
You have one hour

1070
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:04,560
to secretly complete the task

1071
00:33:04,560 --> 00:33:06,240
written on the card with any girl.

1072
00:33:06,240 --> 00:33:07,800
Completing the task within the hour

1073
00:33:07,800 --> 00:33:09,240
means your invitation to her
is successful.

1074
00:33:09,840 --> 00:33:12,400
The secret task must be kept
confidential from the girl throughout.

1075
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:13,440
If the secret is exposed,

1076
00:33:13,440 --> 00:33:14,720
then it is considered
a failed invitation.

1077
00:33:15,360 --> 00:33:16,800
Basically, she can't find out.

1078
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:20,480
Now it's the guys' turn
to initiate invites with the girls.

1079
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:23,160
So if I succeed,
I can extend the invitation.

1080
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:25,360
If I don't succeed, I can't invite her.

1081
00:33:25,360 --> 00:33:26,720
(When I first saw it,)

1082
00:33:26,720 --> 00:33:28,040
(I thought it was okay.)

1083
00:33:28,040 --> 00:33:29,920
Not very difficult.

1084
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:31,080
Because I also saw others

1085
00:33:31,080 --> 00:33:32,600
whose faces were going green.

1086
00:33:34,560 --> 00:33:35,720
(My task)

1087
00:33:35,720 --> 00:33:36,680
(was pretty complex.)

1088
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:39,080
(I hadn't decided
at the time who to invite.)

1089
00:33:39,640 --> 00:33:40,520
What's his task?

1090
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:43,600
Actually, the person
I originally wanted to invite

1091
00:33:43,600 --> 00:33:44,360
was Ruita.

1092
00:33:44,360 --> 00:33:46,000
(Lu Bingkun plans to invite Wang Yi)
I think I should find

1093
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:47,120
a more appropriate way

1094
00:33:47,120 --> 00:33:48,120
to make this invitation.

1095
00:33:50,040 --> 00:33:50,960
I chose to do this task

1096
00:33:50,960 --> 00:33:51,960
with Lvyang.

1097
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:52,840
(Ling Lizheng plans to invite Xu Lvyang)

1098
00:33:52,840 --> 00:33:53,800
The secret invitation task

1099
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:55,600
was to give a piece of jewelry

1100
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:56,680
to one of the girls.

1101
00:33:56,993 --> 00:33:58,120
(Ling Lizheng's secret task:
Give jewelry to one girl)

1102
00:33:58,120 --> 00:33:59,120
But I don't want

1103
00:33:59,120 --> 00:34:00,800
to treat it solely as a task to finish.

1104
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:02,000
I'd like to think of it

1105
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:03,080
as a timely opportunity

1106
00:34:03,480 --> 00:34:04,840
for me to do this thing.

1107
00:34:07,120 --> 00:34:08,280
That scared me.

1108
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:09,200
What's wrong?

1109
00:34:09,200 --> 00:34:10,840
It's okay. The dog gave me a fright.

1110
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:11,800
What are you going to do later?

1111
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:13,720
I thought I'd go downstairs
and play some music.

1112
00:34:14,520 --> 00:34:15,920
How come you still got a notification?

1113
00:34:16,800 --> 00:34:18,400
No, I meant to ask you,

1114
00:34:19,960 --> 00:34:21,360
are you going to be busy later?

1115
00:34:21,360 --> 00:34:22,000
How long will it take?

1116
00:34:22,760 --> 00:34:23,320
Not sure.

1117
00:34:26,320 --> 00:34:28,000
I noticed there's this rooftop

1118
00:34:29,040 --> 00:34:30,080
terrace at the back.

1119
00:34:30,080 --> 00:34:30,760
So,

1120
00:34:31,720 --> 00:34:33,120
once you're done later,

1121
00:34:33,120 --> 00:34:34,080
do you wanna go out for a walk?

1122
00:34:35,480 --> 00:34:36,000
Sure.

1123
00:34:36,000 --> 00:34:36,640
Okay.

1124
00:34:36,640 --> 00:34:37,800
Let me just grab a jacket.

1125
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:38,200
Alright.

1126
00:34:40,768 --> 00:34:41,320
Brother, sit.

1127
00:34:42,040 --> 00:34:42,520
Brother.

1128
00:34:54,880 --> 00:34:55,520
That's a lot of words.

1129
00:34:56,960 --> 00:34:58,080
Our tasks are all different, huh?

1130
00:34:58,080 --> 00:34:58,440
Yeah.

1131
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:00,320
Why is mine so difficult?

1132
00:35:01,480 --> 00:35:02,080
Yours is really tough.

1133
00:35:05,880 --> 00:35:06,480
What is it?

1134
00:35:07,200 --> 00:35:07,776
What?

1135
00:35:07,880 --> 00:35:08,448
Nothing.

1136
00:35:08,680 --> 00:35:09,280
(The task must be kept secret from the girls throughout.)
We...

1137
00:35:09,280 --> 00:35:09,800
(Otherwise, the task fails.)

1138
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:10,920
They can't let her know

1139
00:35:10,920 --> 00:35:12,240
that they're carrying out a task.

1140
00:35:12,240 --> 00:35:12,720
What is it?

1141
00:35:13,960 --> 00:35:15,600
What did Ling Lizheng
call you for earlier?

1142
00:35:16,360 --> 00:35:17,080
To go for a walk.

1143
00:35:17,680 --> 00:35:18,080
And?

1144
00:35:18,080 --> 00:35:18,912
Are you guys going out now?

1145
00:35:19,160 --> 00:35:19,640
Yes.

1146
00:35:21,120 --> 00:35:22,760
I came down to put on some music.

1147
00:35:22,760 --> 00:35:23,960
I'm also asking you out for a walk.

1148
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:25,400
What?

1149
00:35:25,400 --> 00:35:26,360
Did you get a new task card?

1150
00:35:26,360 --> 00:35:27,320
I also ask you out for a walk.

1151
00:35:27,320 --> 00:35:28,840
You guys got new task cards?

1152
